00:11:30,640 --> 00:11:31,917
How are we looking
here, Dr. Karev?

248
00:11:31,941 --> 00:11:33,724
Uh, well, that's not blood.

249
00:11:33,793 --> 00:11:36,521
Oh, no. RUSSO:
Looks like amniotic fluid.

250
00:11:36,545 --> 00:11:38,412
Show me the uterine
fundus, please.

251
00:11:39,916 --> 00:11:42,533
Damn it. Uterus is perforated.

252
00:11:42,602 --> 00:11:45,136
Let me have a look
there. Thank you.

253
00:11:45,204 --> 00:11:47,939
Getting fluid in her abdomen.

254
00:11:48,008 --> 00:11:50,024
This pregnancy has
just become non-viable.

255
00:11:50,092 --> 00:11:52,138
This baby's barely
viable outside that womb.

256
00:11:52,162 --> 00:11:53,728
It's only 24 weeks.

257
00:11:53,796 --> 00:11:55,290
You can repair it, can't you?
- I can try.

258
00:11:55,314 --> 00:11:57,432
Throw in a plasma
patch, hope for the best.

259
00:11:57,501 --> 00:11:59,378
- "Hope for the best"?
- It's experimental.

260
00:11:59,402 --> 00:12:00,996
But if we want to
prolong this pregnancy...

261
00:12:01,020 --> 00:12:03,315
Of course we do. RUSSO:
Then a patch is the way to go.

262
00:12:03,339 --> 00:12:05,467
Five seconds ago,
you wanted to deliver.

263
00:12:05,491 --> 00:12:06,969
Now you're confident
in a plasma patch?

264
00:12:06,993 --> 00:12:09,060
Dr. Karev, I am
the OB on call here.

265
00:12:09,129 --> 00:12:10,511
You are a peds surgeon.

266
00:12:10,580 --> 00:12:13,348
If I say that a patch
is best, a patch is best.

267
00:12:13,416 --> 00:12:14,849
Kepner?

268
00:12:14,918 --> 00:12:17,802
If it keeps the baby
in, I vote for the patch.

269
00:12:17,871 --> 00:12:19,954
Stay in your lane, Dr. Karev.

270
00:12:20,023 --> 00:12:22,540
Prep albumin polymers, please.

271
00:12:22,609 --> 00:12:24,292
I'll update the mom.

272
00:12:38,057 --> 00:12:39,624
How'd it go? How's Jenny?

273
00:12:39,692 --> 00:12:41,604
Well, she's still in
surgery but doing great.

274
00:12:41,628 --> 00:12:43,172
We located the
source of the leak,

275
00:12:43,196 --> 00:12:45,430
and Dr. Russo's
repairing it right now.

276
00:12:45,498 --> 00:12:46,597
And the baby?

277
00:12:46,666 --> 00:12:48,877
The baby is healthy
and still in utero,

278
00:12:48,901 --> 00:12:50,768
which is what we want.

279
00:12:50,837 --> 00:12:53,221
It's too little to
be born, right?

280
00:12:53,289 --> 00:12:54,822
It wouldn't be ideal.

281
00:12:54,891 --> 00:12:59,393
I need you to sign one more
form for Dr. Russo's repair.

282
00:12:59,462 --> 00:13:01,095
It seems like I was just here

283
00:13:01,164 --> 00:13:03,331
