be pretty grueling, I'd imagine.

294
00:13:39,186 --> 00:13:41,080
Actually, it's a
research fellowship,

295
00:13:41,104 --> 00:13:43,137
so it will be far
more predictable

296
00:13:43,223 --> 00:13:44,822
than a surgery
resident's schedule.

297
00:13:44,891 --> 00:13:46,891
Oh, I see.

298
00:13:46,959 --> 00:13:49,227
What was Sofia
wearing this morning?

299
00:13:49,279 --> 00:13:50,856
What? What was
she wearing today?

300
00:13:50,880 --> 00:13:51,896
I...

301
00:13:53,399 --> 00:13:55,377
I don't know. You didn't
see her this morning?

302
00:13:55,401 --> 00:13:57,952
No, I did. I just...

303
00:13:58,020 --> 00:14:00,704
I can't, uh, recall
exactly what it...

304
00:14:00,773 --> 00:14:02,156
Objection. Relevance.

305
00:14:02,224 --> 00:14:03,624
Moving on.

306
00:14:03,693 --> 00:14:05,960
What grade is Sofia in?

307
00:14:06,029 --> 00:14:07,545
Second.

308
00:14:07,614 --> 00:14:08,614
No, first.

309
00:14:10,282 --> 00:14:12,299
She's in first grade.

310
00:14:12,368 --> 00:14:15,619
I have to go, and this
is getting hard to watch.

311
00:14:16,439 --> 00:14:17,683
Are you sure? PENNY: Yes.

312
00:14:17,707 --> 00:14:19,134
Because you didn't sound sure,

313
00:14:19,158 --> 00:14:21,053
and you keep saying this
is a child that you know,

314
00:14:21,077 --> 00:14:24,028
a child that you're
gonna soon co-parent.

315
00:14:25,331 --> 00:14:26,675
I can see how you
might not remember

316
00:14:26,699 --> 00:14:28,060
what color tutu she
wore to school today,

317
00:14:28,084 --> 00:14:29,745
but to not even know
what grade she's in...

318
00:14:29,769 --> 00:14:32,820
So many objections.
Badgering, irrelevant...

319
00:14:32,889 --> 00:14:34,622
Sustained. I'm sorry.

320
00:14:34,690 --> 00:14:36,452
I don't mean to belabor the
point, but you said it yourself.

321
00:14:36,476 --> 00:14:38,754
You've only known
Sofia a few months, so...

322
00:14:38,778 --> 00:14:40,298
No, that is not what I meant.

323
00:14:40,346 --> 00:14:42,706
But that is what you said.

324
00:14:43,333 --> 00:14:45,016
All right, Counselor.

325
00:14:45,085 --> 00:14:46,884
I know what grade she's in.

326
00:14:46,953 --> 00:14:48,836
I do. I do.

327
00:14:48,905 --> 00:14:50,985
No further questions,
Your Honor.

328
00:15:10,843 --> 00:15:13,255
Maybe it wasn't that bad.

329
00:15:13,279 --> 00:15:15,319
That was really, really bad.

330
00:15:15,398 --> 00:15:18,399
Oh, God.

331
00:15:18,467 --> 00:15:20,484
But it doesn't kill us. Not yet.

332
00:15:20,553 --> 00:15:22,998
I can't believe Arizona
let them pull that slimy bull.

333
00:15:23,022 --> 00:15:24,538
It was a smart
move, and it worked.

334
00:15:24,607 --> 00:15:25,767
But we've got smarter moves.

335
00:15:25,808 --> 00:15:27,536
I'm gonna put Dr. Grey
on the stand tomorrow,

336
00:15:27,560 --> 00:15:29,293
and she's gonna close strong.

337
00:15:29,362 --> 00:15:30,728
Look confident.

338
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:36,200
You're the Chief of Surgery.

339
00:15:36,269 --> 00:15:38,669
Doctors Torres and
Robbins report to you.

340
00:15:38,738 --> 00:15:40,138
That is correct.

341
00:15:40,206 --> 00:15:42,184
And for those of us
who aren't surgeons,

342
00:15:42,208 --> 00:15:44,019
Dr. Torres operates on bones

343
00:15:44,043 --> 00:15:45,588
while Dr. Robbins
operates on babies.

344
00:15:45,612 --> 00:15:46,655
Is that correct?

345
00:15:46,679 --> 00:15:48,179
Well, fetuses and babies.

346
00:15:48,247 --> 00:15:49,681
Yes.

347
00:15:49,749 --> 00:15:51,026
How does the schedule
of an orthopedic surgeon

348
00:15:51,050 --> 00:15:52,861
compare to that
of a fetal surgeon?

349
00:15:52,885 --> 00:15:54,480
Well, it varies day to day.

350
00:15:54,504 --> 00:15:55,998
I see, but in your opinion,

351
00:15:56,022 --> 00:15:59,423
which specialty has more
unscheduled surgeries?

352
00:15:59,492 --> 00:16:02,309
Ortho or fetal? There's
really no comparison.

353
00:16:02,378 --> 00:16:04,156
But Dr. Robbins'
schedule is dictated

354
00:16:04,180 --> 00:16:06,813
by the unpredictable
nature of childbirth, is it not?

355
00:16:06,882 --> 00:16:08,562
Objection. Speculation.

356
00:16:09,485 --> 00:16:12,754
She can't do that.
You can't do that.

357
00:16:12,822 --> 00:16:14,822
I asked if Dr. Robbins' schedule

358
00:16:14,891 --> 00:16:18,276
is dictated by the
unpredictable nature of childbirth.

359
00:16:18,345 --> 00:16:20,189
Objection. Speculation.

360
00:16:20,213 --> 00:16:23,175
Your Honor, I'm asking an
expert witness her opinion.

361
00:16:23,199 --> 00:16:25,611
It's only speculation if
counsel is calling into question

362
00:16:25,635 --> 00:16:27,279
the expertise of
this witness as Chief.

363
00:16:27,303 --> 00:16:29,186
Overruled. Counselor, proceed.

364
00:16:29,255 --> 00:16:32,655
Dr. Robbins' schedule is
unpredictable, wouldn't you say?

365
00:16:35,661 --> 00:16:37,428
It can be, yes. Any surgeon's...

366
00:16:37,497 --> 00:16:40,192
Sure, but how many unscheduled
emergency procedures

367
00:16:40,216 --> 00:16:42,816
did Dr. Robbins log
over the past six months?

368
00:16:42,885 --> 00:16:44,268
I have no idea.

369
00:16:44,337 --> 00:16:47,038
I would like to introduce
into evidence Document 2C.

370
00:16:51,744 --> 00:16:53,838
Take a look. This might
refresh your memory.

371
00:16:53,862 --> 00:16:55,106
What is that report, Doctor?

372
00:16:55,130 --> 00:16:59,266
This is a list of emergency
procedures performed

373
00:16:59,335 --> 00:17:02,753
by Dr. Robbins and Dr. Torres
for the past six months.

374
00:17:02,822 --> 00:17:04,200
And according to that document,

375
00:17:04,224 --> 00:17:07,175
how many emergency
procedures did Dr. Torres log

376
00:17:07,243 --> 00:17:08,575
in the past six months?

377
00:17:10,914 --> 00:17:13,380
Twenty-seven. Twenty-seven.

378
00:17:13,449 --> 00:17:15,649
And how many did
Dr. Robbins log?

379
00:17:20,924 --> 00:17:22,039
Ninety-two.

380
00:17:22,992 --> 00:17:24,542
Ninety-two.

381
00:17:24,610 --> 00:17:25,910
Now, even for a surgeon,

382
00:17:25,978 --> 00:17:27,923
wouldn't you call that
kind of schedule grueling?

383
00:17:27,947 --> 00:17:29,413
You can say that. I wouldn't.

384
00:17:29,482 --> 00:17:31,682
I would say it's
wildly successful,

385
00:17:31,751 --> 00:17:34,552
but then, I would never
put a woman's success

386
00:17:34,621 --> 00:17:36,136
in the con column.

387
00:17:36,205 --> 00:17:38,133
What about her daughter, though?

388
00:17:38,157 --> 00:17:39,234
Ninety-two.

389
00:17:39,258 --> 00:17:41,542
Ninety-two times she
dropped everything,

390
00:17:41,611 --> 00:17:45,362
Sofia included, to go to a job.

391
00:17:45,431 --> 00:17:47,247
Would you ask that
if she were a man?

392
00:17:49,468 --> 00:17:52,419
Ninety-two times she
chose work over her child.

393
00:17:52,488 --> 00:17:53,670
Your Honor...

394
00:17:53,739 --> 00:17:56,907
Ninety-two times
Dr. Robbins was saving babies,

395
00:17:56,976 --> 00:17:59,393
saving parents from
losing their own children!

396
00:18:00,864 --> 00:18:02,597
No further questions.

397
00:18:04,100 --> 00:18:05,466
Don't get discouraged.

398
00:18:05,535 --> 00:18:08,680
They're trying to turn your
strength into weakness.

399
00:18:11,557 --> 00:18:14,158
This court is adjourned
until tomorrow.

400
00:18:21,467 --> 00:18:23,301
No, over here. Right
up against the bed.

401
00:18:23,369 --> 00:18:25,702
God, Mom. Just go home to sleep.

402
00:18:25,771 --> 00:18:27,338
This is so embarrassing.

403
00:18:27,407 --> 00:18:29,067
I'm sorry. She's a nightmare.

404
00:18:29,091 --> 00:18:32,009
That's right. I'm
everybody's nightmare.

405
00:18:32,078 --> 00:18:33,722
Can I have another blanket, please?
- Sure.

406
00:18:33,746 --> 00:18:35,730
Hey! How's everyone feeling?

407
00:18:35,798 --> 00:18:37,732
I hear you're
sleeping over tonight.

408
00:18:37,800 --> 00:18:40,061
Thank God you're back. She's
nicer to me when you're around.

409
00:18:40,085 --> 00:18:41,285
Surgery went well?

410
00:18:41,354 --> 00:18:42,869
Yeah. Russo did a plasma patch.

411
00:18:42,938 --> 00:18:45,957
Yeah, that's a good call.
This baby needs more time.

412
00:18:46,025 --> 00:18:48,403
Okay, listen. I'm sorry that I
wasn't here for the surgery,

413
00:18:48,427 --> 00:18:50,828
but I'll be checking
in later, okay?

414
00:18:54,734 --> 00:18:56,600
I told you. Kepner and
I have Jenny handled.

415
00:18:56,669 --> 00:18:58,869
She's doing fine. The baby's
good. Everyone's stable.

416
00:18:58,938 --> 00:19:00,237
Um, where's Russo?

417
00:19:00,306 --> 00:19:01,171
I need to look at a
post-op ultrasound

418
00:19:01,224 --> 00:19:02,333
to make sure the leak is sealed.

419
00:19:02,357 --> 00:19:03,924
Should you be here?

420
00:19:03,993 --> 00:19:06,154
Shouldn't you be at home getting
ready for court or something?

421
00:19:06,178 --> 00:19:07,356
No. I shouldn't be here.

422
00:19:07,380 --> 00:19:09,146
I should be at home

423
00:19:09,215 --> 00:19:10,609
fixing my daughter ice cream
and reading her <i>Charlotte's Web.</i>

424
00:19:10,633 --> 00:19:12,444
So could you please page Russo

425
00:19:12,468 --> 00:19:14,596
so I can look at the ultrasounds
and get the hell out of here?

426
00:19:14,620 --> 00:19:15,636
Okay.

427
00:19:15,704 --> 00:19:16,937
Thank you.

428
00:19:20,276 --> 00:19:21,954
It's an impossible situation.

429
00:19:21,978 --> 00:19:23,622
A break-up is tough
enough as it is,

430
00:19:23,646 --> 00:19:25,090
but with a kid in the mix...

431
00:19:25,114 --> 00:19:27,314
I can't even imagine.

432
00:19:27,383 --> 00:19:29,160
