444
00:19:50,490 --> 00:19:51,856
Hey! Steph, look at me.

445
00:19:51,924 --> 00:19:54,241
You have 10 more
seconds to talk about him,

446
00:19:54,310 --> 00:19:56,043
and then no more Kyle talk.

447
00:19:56,112 --> 00:19:58,245
I said that to you. I know.

448
00:19:58,314 --> 00:20:00,347
Ten, nine...

449
00:20:00,416 --> 00:20:02,177
Shut up. I'm calling him.

450
00:20:02,201 --> 00:20:04,634
And it is not
drunk-dialing, sir.

451
00:20:04,703 --> 00:20:07,070
It is me undoing my mistake.

452
00:20:07,139 --> 00:20:08,522
Okay. I...

453
00:20:08,590 --> 00:20:10,691
Give it back. No.

454
00:20:10,760 --> 00:20:12,604
You are a good friend.

455
00:20:12,628 --> 00:20:13,628
I know.

456
00:20:17,182 --> 00:20:19,662
So, what were you thinking?

457
00:20:19,818 --> 00:20:21,218
Okay, um...

458
00:20:22,288 --> 00:20:23,987
When the baby's born...

459
00:20:24,056 --> 00:20:25,405
Starting Day 1, huh?

460
00:20:25,474 --> 00:20:29,643
I would like to be in
the room for the birth.

461
00:20:29,712 --> 00:20:32,580
So if that makes you
uncomfortable... No, not at all.

462
00:20:33,683 --> 00:20:35,248
Really? Yeah.

463
00:20:35,317 --> 00:20:36,557
Yeah, I want you there.

464
00:20:36,586 --> 00:20:38,603
Okay, um...

465
00:20:38,671 --> 00:20:41,138
Well, when the baby's
on a feeding schedule,

466
00:20:41,207 --> 00:20:43,624
whenever that happens,
then I'm thinking weekends?

467
00:20:43,692 --> 00:20:44,953
You don't want
to split the week?

468
00:20:44,977 --> 00:20:46,410
I do. Yes.

469
00:20:46,479 --> 00:20:47,719
But when the baby's older,

470
00:20:47,780 --> 00:20:49,124
we may need to switch
to every other week.

471
00:20:49,148 --> 00:20:51,359
I've read that that is
just... Easier on the child.

472
00:20:51,383 --> 00:20:52,733
Yeah, I read that, too.

473
00:20:52,801 --> 00:20:54,763
But I want Easter.
It's important to me.

474
00:20:54,787 --> 00:20:57,933
I go to church, and you...
Worship the Easter bunny.

475
00:20:57,957 --> 00:20:59,707
Right.

476
00:20:59,775 --> 00:21:01,509
Now, are we talking
Easter egg hunts

477
00:21:01,577 --> 00:21:02,776
or just church?

478
00:21:02,845 --> 00:21:04,273
Yeah, of course there
will be an Easter egg hunt.

479
00:21:04,297 --> 00:21:07,598
All right, then
Easter's all yours.

480
00:21:07,667 --> 00:21:09,945
Uh, and you can have the
Super Bowl and Halloween.

481
00:21:09,969 --> 00:21:11,969
Mmm, sure.

