625
00:27:38,056 --> 00:27:39,490
Uh, yes, that's
correct. Mmm-hmm.

626
00:27:39,558 --> 00:27:42,103
Would you say there's overlap
between your specialties?

627
00:27:42,127 --> 00:27:43,277
Yes, there is.

628
00:27:43,362 --> 00:27:45,963
So, you two have gotten
close over the years.

629
00:27:46,031 --> 00:27:47,951
Professionally. We have. Yes.

630
00:27:54,556 --> 00:27:55,796
Are you a trivia buff?

631
00:27:58,694 --> 00:28:00,043
Yes.

632
00:28:00,112 --> 00:28:02,457
So, you and Dr. Robbins have
enjoyed trivia nights together.

633
00:28:02,481 --> 00:28:03,514
That's correct, yes.

634
00:28:03,582 --> 00:28:05,693
You go and play, drink,
and flirt with women.

635
00:28:05,717 --> 00:28:07,062
Is that correct? No, it isn't.

636
00:28:07,086 --> 00:28:08,818
I'm married and I don't drink.

637
00:28:08,888 --> 00:28:10,415
So Dr. Robbins did all
the drinking and flirting.

638
00:28:10,439 --> 00:28:12,116
You just went for the trivia?

639
00:28:12,140 --> 00:28:15,275
That's an over-simplified... It's a
yes or no question, Dr. Webber.

640
00:28:15,344 --> 00:28:18,344
Yes. You're good at trivia?

641
00:28:18,647 --> 00:28:20,291
Sure. Don't be modest.

642
00:28:20,315 --> 00:28:22,949
How many times do you think
you and Dr. Robbins have won

643
00:28:23,018 --> 00:28:25,047
over the past, oh,
let's say, six months?

644
00:28:25,071 --> 00:28:26,948
I wasn't counting. The bar was.

