659
00:29:04,510 --> 00:29:06,053
Callie and I swap all the time.

660
00:29:06,077 --> 00:29:08,729
We have very flexible
schedules. Shh.

661
00:29:08,797 --> 00:29:10,608
Could you please tell the court

662
00:29:10,632 --> 00:29:12,165
the tally at the bottom?

663
00:29:15,337 --> 00:29:17,221
Dr. Webber?

664
00:29:18,624 --> 00:29:19,868
Thirty-four. Thirty-four.

665
00:29:19,892 --> 00:29:23,594
She asked Dr. Torres to
switch with her 34 times.

666
00:29:23,662 --> 00:29:26,525
We know she was out
with you at least 25 times.

667
00:29:26,549 --> 00:29:28,543
And that's in addition to
the previously mentioned

668
00:29:28,567 --> 00:29:31,384
ninety-two times
Dr. Robbins was unavailable

669
00:29:31,453 --> 00:29:34,416
to parent her own child due
to her professional demands.

670
00:29:34,440 --> 00:29:38,058
Now, let's just pause and
think about this for a minute.

671
00:29:38,144 --> 00:29:41,077
There are only 180
days in six months' time,

672
00:29:41,146 --> 00:29:43,864
and so far, we've counted
approximately 150 times

673
00:29:43,932 --> 00:29:46,010
in which Dr. Robbins
shirked her duties.

674
00:29:46,034 --> 00:29:47,900
150 out of 180.

675
00:29:47,969 --> 00:29:49,765
Objection. Badgering
the witness.

676
00:29:49,789 --> 00:29:52,322
Calls for speculation.
Sustained.

677
00:29:52,390 --> 00:29:55,341
Your Honor, we'd like
to request a short recess.

678
00:30:04,870 --> 00:30:06,347
So, Callie's okay
slut-shaming me now?

679
00:30:06,371 --> 00:30:08,221
Don't let them rattle you.

680
00:30:08,290 --> 00:30:10,134
They're making it sound like
a working mom is a bad mom.

681
00:30:10,158 --> 00:30:11,502
I mean, we just
lost in there, right?

682
00:30:11,526 --> 00:30:12,703
'Cause they made me sound like

683
00:30:12,727 --> 00:30:15,323
I was a selfish,
irresponsible, sex-crazed...

684
00:30:15,347 --> 00:30:17,187
Arizona. Stop. I don't...

685
00:30:17,850 --> 00:30:19,582
You have your chance right now.

686
00:30:19,651 --> 00:30:21,318
They tried to rewrite the story.

687
00:30:21,386 --> 00:30:23,069
Now's your chance
to set it straight.

688
00:30:23,138 --> 00:30:26,390
You need to get up
there, tell them the truth.

689
00:30:26,458 --> 00:30:27,724
Judge Kane is smart.

690
00:30:27,793 --> 00:30:29,860
She'll know the truth
when she hears it.

691
00:30:29,928 --> 00:30:32,612
You tell the truth,
and you will win this.

692
00:30:34,983 --> 00:30:37,645
When Sofia was born, how
did that day start for you?

693
00:30:39,704 --> 00:30:41,604
I was in a car accident.

694
00:30:44,126 --> 00:30:47,511
Can you tell us what you
remember about the accident?

695
00:30:47,580 --> 00:30:50,814
I don't remember
much, but I remember...

696
00:30:52,484 --> 00:30:54,585
I remember waking up
on the hood of the car

697
00:30:55,987 --> 00:30:58,955
and I was covered in glass.

698
00:31:00,593 --> 00:31:02,892
I was, um, barely...

699
00:31:02,961 --> 00:31:04,494
I'm so sorry.

700
00:31:06,214 --> 00:31:08,374
Take all the time you need.

701
00:31:19,194 --> 00:31:21,962
I was barely conscious, um,

702
00:31:22,030 --> 00:31:25,565
and the only thing that I
could feel was just pain all over.

703
00:31:28,136 --> 00:31:32,205
I could have died on
the hood of that car.

704
00:31:32,274 --> 00:31:34,741
And I wanted to give up.

705
00:31:34,810 --> 00:31:37,027
But...

706
00:31:37,096 --> 00:31:39,596
I couldn't because I
was pregnant with Sofia.

707
00:31:41,666 --> 00:31:44,801
And if I died, she died.

708
00:31:45,871 --> 00:31:47,237
So...

709
00:31:48,707 --> 00:31:50,040
I had to fight

710
00:31:51,377 --> 00:31:54,278
to stay alive, for
my daughter's sake.

711
00:31:57,816 --> 00:32:00,284
Being a mother is the
reason I'm still alive today.

712
00:32:16,902 --> 00:32:18,813
Jenny, your BP's borderline low,

713
00:32:18,837 --> 00:32:21,505
but otherwise, your
cardiac evaluation is good.

714
00:32:21,573 --> 00:32:23,184
So, she's cleared for surgery.

715
00:32:23,208 --> 00:32:25,353
Surgery. What surgery?
What happened?

716
00:32:25,377 --> 00:32:27,778
Dr. Russo says
we have to deliver.

717
00:32:27,846 --> 00:32:29,791
Jenny's still leaking
amniotic fluid,

718
00:32:29,815 --> 00:32:31,476
which means we're out of time.

719
00:32:31,500 --> 00:32:33,500
We need to do a
C-section, deliver this baby.

720
00:32:33,568 --> 00:32:35,446
Right now? It's
too early, right?

721
00:32:35,470 --> 00:32:38,037
It's not ideal, but
there may be no choice.

722
00:32:38,106 --> 00:32:39,772
Please don't. Not yet.

723
00:32:39,841 --> 00:32:41,102
I don't want my baby to die.

724
00:32:41,126 --> 00:32:42,976
Honey, everything
is gonna be fine.

725
00:32:43,045 --> 00:32:44,245
Can I see you outside?

726
00:32:49,401 --> 00:32:51,067
